40|$|We examine why banks {{resort to}} collateral, and whether their reasons vary {{according}} to the type <b>of</b> <b>collateral.</b> We use a unique dataset of bank loans granted to French distressed firms, which contains full information on the type and <b>value</b> <b>of</b> <b>collaterals</b> and the cause of firm default. Our work suggests that information asymmetries are not of prime importance in the decision of the bank to secure a loan, as no type <b>of</b> <b>collateral</b> helps to solve adverse selection and moral hazard problems. The reduction of the loan loss and the observed-risk hypothesis may however explain the use <b>of</b> <b>collateral.</b> Collateral, Bank, Credit Risk. ...|$|R
