50|$|Another {{topic of}} {{study is the}} impact of sudden stops on output. Sudden stops can be {{accompanied}} by a currency crisis and/or a banking crisis. Empirical studies show that the effects of a banking crisis are more pernicious than the effects of a currency crisis, due to the additional effect of the credit channel on output. Lower asset prices are a persistent fact after a banking crisis, which indicate a low <b>value</b> <b>of</b> <b>collaterals</b> to loans, and therefore, negatively impact the banking sector and the supply of loans.|$|R
